name: Village Inn
directions: Back left, with the other restrooms
comment: Paying customers only

name: Jos. A. Bank
directions: Back of store

name: Upland Tap House
directions: In the back near the rear entrance
comment: Two gender neutral single stall restrooms with locking doors.

name: Cassava
directions: It's in the back; walk in, go through the back, past the kitchen.

name: Rockaway Brewing Company
directions: Bathrooms in the back by the pinball machine, more bathrooms upstairs, stairs are just past the first bathrooms
comment: Any age, brewery only cards when buying drinks, not on entrance.

name: Northampton College
directions: A few different ones throughout the college, and the ones that are there are mainly next to the gendered toilets.
comment: You can only use if you are a visitor at college or if you attend the college but I thought it might be helpful anyway so that people can know

name: Daddio's
directions: Unisex single stall bathrooms. One by pool tables and one at the end of bar as you first come in. Both have a ladies sign on them, but that is just to let you know that there is a bathroom there.

name: Castle Remedies
comment: 1st Floor

name: Humane Society Thrift Store
directions: Go in and through the store to back store

name: Marks & Spencer
directions: At the back of the cafe, down some steps and past tables, or around past the counter and their is a ramp.
comment: Two large, non-gendered disabled-access toilets. They're the only toilets by the cafe, so you won't get a strange look for using the disabled without apparent cause.

name: The Brewing Market
directions: From the front door, veer toward the left around the counter to the back of the building. There are two single bathrooms with locks (labeled Male/Female), one or your left and another on your right.
comment: Probably supposed to be a customer- just exit out the back door between the signle bathrooms.

name: Centra
directions: By the food freezer
comment: Ok for anyone to use

name: Rutland city free library
directions: Two unisex bathrooms, get the key by the front desk.

name: Starbucks coffee
directions: Straight in next to the tables on the left
comment: Easy to access without being a paying customer

name: costa coffee
directions: Straight in next to the counter
comment: You should be a paying customer but it's easy to access it without paying anything

name: The double knot
directions: In the back of the first floor, to the left. Second bathroom in the basement, all the way at the back
comment: It's kind of a yuppie bar, walk to the back of the top floor like you're meeting people.

name: Barnes & Noble
comment: Barnes & Noble has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

name: Starbucks
comment: Starbucks has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

comment: Starbucks has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

comment: Starbucks has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

comment: Starbucks has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

name: Starbucks
comment: Starbucks has a transgender friendly bathroom policy.

name: 780 Lincoln Ave, Napa, CA 94558, USA
comment:
This is a combined VOICES Youth Center and LGBTQ Center. Our house of operations are; 
Monday: Closed
Tuesday: 10am-6pm
Wednesday: 10am-6pm
Thursday: 12pm-6pm
Friday: 10am-6pm

name: Grand Casino Hinckley
directions: Next to the pool in the casino.  From the Casino hotel lobby follow the hanging sings that point to the pool.  It is not in the pool, but on the opposite wall of where the pool enterance doors are.
comment: The pool is closed, so in a few months the bathroom may not be accessible due to construction.

name: School of Rock McKinney
comment: You need to be either a student or picking up a student to use it

name: The Kiln Drive-In
directions: In the front half of the parlor on the left hand side near the cash and credit till
comment: You probably have to order something but you could just slip in and use it and ask for directions

name: ADIO Health Systems
directions: Two unisex bathrooms near back of building. Clearly labeled
comment: Chiropractic patient preferred. Will not be turned away in an emergency

name: Smashburger
directions: Gendered single stall. Just past IHOP, same complex as Torrid and House of Cupcakes.
comment: You should probably buy something. (They sell bottled water and other beverages right up front. )

name: Nordstoroms at the grove
directions: 2nd floor near the elevator in women's department

name: BOOM Concepts
directions: Our bathroom is accessible, but we do not always have the ramp at our front door to make the main entrance to the building wheel-chair accessible.

name: Van's BBQ
comment: Only one restroom in the entire place, probably not LGBTQ friendly

name: Kitsuné Espresso Bar
directions: Single stall gender neutral restroom at the back of the café.  Ask if you can use the restroom if you're not a paying customer, but they're probably going to say yes (I saw someone come in and ask if they could just use the restroom, and the barista had no issue with it).  The bathroom is fairly narrow, so I doubt a wheelchair would be able to get in.

name: Los Sabrosos Dance Co.
directions: Both bathrooms in the back of the dance studio are unisex and welcome to all.
comment: come take a lesson or stay for a dance night!

name: Star Gate
directions: By entrance of Outdoor Crazy Golf
comment: Costs 20p

name: Schouwburg Almere / De Kunstlinie
directions: Down the left hall then to the right.
comment: It's one bathroom area with 4 stalls; 2 are male and 2 are female, but the stickers that indicate gender are almost scraped off and no one pays attention to them.

name: Sister Louisa's Church of the Living Room & Ping Pong Emporium
directions: The sign on every restroom is, "Whichever."
comment:
https://www.sisterlouisaschurch.com/
Hours
Mon-Fri: 5pm-3am
Sat: 5pm-3am
Sun: 3pm-midnight
Phone
(404) 522-8275

name: Exploratorium
directions: To the right of gendered bathrooms near information desk.
comment: This bathroom is inside the paid area.

name: Market Commons Public Bathrooms
directions: Right outside of the parking garage, in front of the bicycle shop, there are 2 public stalls. Both unisex, lockable doors,  spacious.
comment: Open to public

name: Cafe Rhubarb
directions: Near the petrol station, next to the Dental Care
comment: Mandy who runs the cafe is very nice, so you should be able to just use the toilet if you ask :)

name: Target
comment: I haven't been there myself but a friend said it was okay to use and the people there were kind to them so I hope this is helpful <3

name: Bennett family house
comment: This is my house so emergency's only please

name: Mixtape
directions: All five restrooms in this boozy coffeehouse / bar are single occupant-gender inclusive. There is one accessible restroom upstairs and 4 more down the front stairs.

name: Five Guys
directions: Two gendered, single-use restrooms in the hallway at the rear of the restaurant.

name: People's Food Co-Op
directions: In the cafe area
comment: Do not need to be a paying customer

name: POWER
directions: Back of the building, there's a door right before you get to the kitchen
comment: You must be a client or otherwise involved in their services to use, and it's a single stall restroom.

name: Village Inn
directions: Back of the restaurant, east side. Next to the male/female bathrooms.
comment: i don't know if there is a policy about being a customer- but the staff has always been friendly so...

name: Cardiff castle
directions: First floor of the ticket office
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Cardiff castle
directions: First floor of the ticket office
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Gallery K
directions: Back left corner of the front room
comment: Art Gallery and Coffee House, very LGBT/queer friendly. Non-gendered single stall.

name: Rogers Hall
directions: Ground level, adjacent to the side entrance and next to women's restroom

name: Historic Ashland Armory
directions: Straight through the front doors and to the left.
comment: Probably only open for events which seems to be pretty often.

name: The Fat Dog
directions: Back of the outside bar
comment: In a restaurant

name: Bubble Boba
directions: Enter Bubble Boba, bathroom to the left.

name: Garden and Soul
directions: Off the back room.  You can park in the free public parking and walk across the street to the plaza, and this is one of the first shops.

name: Greens Beverages
directions: Beer and wine side of the store

name: Moosewood Restaurant
directions: Two single restrooms behind the main desk
comment: Restaurant serves vegan and vegetarian lunch and dinner. Might need to pay or ask to use.

name: Yolo Frozen Yogurt
directions: Left side, behind cash counter.
comment: Paying customers only, but is a nongender single stall.

name: Home/made kitchen cafe
directions: Towards the back.
comment: Don't need to eat at the restaurant. Just get a coffee and go to the back.

name: Aldi
directions: Past the check-out stations, east side
comment:
Single user, gendered

It's for customers but if you're bold, you could maybe get in and out without a fuss.

name: Los Cuates
directions: Great restaurant serving regional classic New Mexico foods.

name: FIVE-STAR FoodMart #2215
comment: Single stall locking door with toilet and urinal. Nice people.

name: The Brown Jug Hotel
directions: Enter the gambling section of the Hotel.
comment: Unfortunately, you may be required to buy a drink or two or perhaps put a dollar or Two in the gaming machines under good faith.

name: TATE's COMICS + TOYS + MORE
directions: Underneath the stairs

name: The Cheesecake Factory
directions: Right from the entrance
comment: Preferred paying customer

name: Kentucky Science Center
directions:
Third floor "Timezone Gallery" on the western side of the building, towards the river. Across from the Gravball game.
Also in "Science in Play West immediately past the ticket desk and to the left. Two single-person non-gendered rooms.
comment: Must be museum patron.

name: Julius Meinl
directions: Two restrooms. One labeled women, the other labeled men and women.

name: Marin County Community mental health
directions: First floor to left

name: Sorrento's
directions: On the left of the giant sub picture

name: LGBT Center of Raleigh
directions: In the back hallway, desk staff can direct
comment: The front of the building is not wheelchair accessible, but there is a wheelchair ramp in the back of the building. Calling the front desk, someone can let you in. 2 gender neutral single occupancy restrooms, 2 gendered multi stall restrooms.

name: The Flying Goat
directions: Ask for a code, it switches.
comment: It's single gender neutral stall. If you look at all homeless they will make you purchase something. Expect to spend 1.25 at the least on a cookie, to 3.00 on coffee

name: Club Oasis
directions: Walk in the single door off the smoking porch, go in then take a left and the bathroom will be on the left.
comment: We're an alcoholics anonymous club house, but you can just walk in to use the bathroom if you want to. Extremely doubtful that anyone would question you.

name: Lafayette County & Oxford Public Library
directions: Ask at the Circulation Desk, please.

name: Target
directions: To the left of the non-neutral bathrooms
comment: Safe and accepting.

name: Emporia State University Memorial Union
directions: Two single-room restrooms on the third floor of the Memorial Union. Can take stairs or elevator. Restrooms are located next to journalism offices and student senate room.
comment:
There is also a safe area on first floor - Diversity/PRIDE lounge located next to the elevator and stairs.
Restrooms are large with very little traffic, doors are lockable.

name: Ocoee Middle School
directions: There are two sets of gendered single stall bathrooms. One is in the music hall and the other near the Tech lab.
comment: Not exactly a Trans positive place, but no one makes a if deal out of the single stall restrooms.

name: Nerdist Showroom
directions: By the back on the right.
comment: Browse, ask some questions, be friendly, or buy a $1 comic book. Won't be an issue.

name: Skrapan Mall
directions: Street level, next to the Monki shop
comment: Free for everyone. Three single bathrooms, one bigger for wheelchairs.

name: Elevation Burger
directions: In the back, kind of tucked in the corner.
comment: You're supposed to be a paying customer but it's pretty much not enforced.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store.
comment: The passcode is 12345. There are a lot of people so it won't matter if you can't buy anything--if you just confidently walk to the back, no one will stop you. :)
